metadata.description: Russia Shadow Fleet - Sanctioned Vessels Database
metadata.note: IMO numbers are primary identifiers. MMSI lookup required for real-time matching.

vessels.name: FITBURG
vessels.notes: SUSPECT #1 - Elisa FEC cable sabotage Dec 31, 2025. ANCHOR DRAG CONFIRMED. Track shows 74% speed reduction through cable zone. Departed St. Petersburg Dec 30. Currently anchored Ingå. ISM: SARFO DENIZCILIK (Turkey).

vessels.name: INDRI
vessels.notes: SUSPECT #2 - Elisa FEC investigation Dec 31, 2025. 9 track points over cable route. Multiple CRITICAL alerts. Sierra Leone flag of convenience. Transited cable zone 03:00-04:30 UTC. Currently anchored 59.76°N 24.80°E.

vessels.name: COLD STREAM
vessels.notes: SUSPECT #3 - Elisa FEC investigation Dec 31, 2025. Track crossed cable route at slow speed. 2 CRITICAL alerts. Liberia flag. Last port: Ust-Luga (Russia). Currently anchored near Tallinn 59.49°N 24.59°E.

vessels.name: ZHENG ZHI
vessels.notes: SUSPECT #4 - Elisa FEC investigation Dec 31, 2025. 13 transits through incident zone in 48h. Panama flag. Chinese-named vessel. Erratic navigation pattern. Currently anchored 59.74°N 24.54°E.

vessels.name: SYMPHONY
vessels.notes: Known for transmitting fake IMO numbers

vessels.name: LADY R
vessels.notes: Weapons transport, AIS disabled since Jan 2024

vessels.name: GURU
vessels.notes: 10-hour dark event in English Channel Nov 2025
